sections.Career:
Christie grew up in the village of Small Dole within England's South Downs. As an adult, Christie is 6'3&quot; in height (192 cm). She almost reached her full adult height by the time she was only 14 years old, but rejected the growth inhibitors offered by her doctor. She attended Henfield Primary School, then Warden Park Secondary School, and has said her height made it difficult to fit in. With her real life &quot;very quiet, sedate, and bookish&quot;, she saw film as an exciting view of a wider world, and eventually moved to London to attend drama school.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.net-a-porter.com/magazine/273/20 ]&lt;/ref&gt;

Christie had several minor roles in films such as ''[[wikipedia:The Imaginarium of Doctor Parnassus|The Imaginarium of Doctor Parnassus]]'', before being cast as Brienne in ''Game of Thrones'', her first major role.

Subsequently to joining ''Game of Thrones'', she has been cast in ''[[Wikipedia:The Hunger Games: Mockingjay â&euro;&ldquo; Part 2|The Hunger Games: Mockingjay â&euro;&ldquo; Part 2]]'' (alongside fellow ''Game of Thrones'' actress [[Natalie Dormer]]). On June 2, 2014, it was announced that Christie will appear in ''[[Wikipedia:Star Wars: The Force Awakens|Star Wars Episode VII.]]''.&lt;ref&gt;[http://starwars.com/star-wars-episode-vii-adds-academy-award-winner-lupita-nyongo-and-game-of-thrones-gwendoline-christie.html StarWars.com], June 2, 2014.&lt;/ref&gt;

